Sql vs mongo

Sql is relational database
Sql use structured tables to store data in row
suitable for application with well-defined schemas and fixed data structures
E-commerce platform, HR Management etc
example: MySql, PostgreSQL, Oracle

MonogDB is non-relational database
It provides flexibility scalability varied with data structure and types
Ideal for application with dynamic and evolving data models
CMS, Social Media, Gaming

<!-- Mongo DB Terminolgies -->

In a single data base we can have multiple collections and multiple collections

documents in the form of JSON which is called document oriented

document can also be schemaless

<!-- By using ordered: false the correct documents will added and the error will be thrown -->

<!-- Fields name are case sensative in collections name -->

all the name must be in same manner like if we have used small letter for one and then we have to use same for others

<!-- Read Operations in mongoDB -->

db.collectionName.find()

To find one document

db.collectionName.findOne()

To findMany documents

db.collectionName.findMany()

To find using specific data

db.collectionName.findOne({name: "Vinay"})

To find all data using specific data

db.collectionName.find({name: "Vinay"})

<!-- Import JSON in MongoDb -->

<!-- Update in mongodb -->

<!-- The first parameter is id and the second parameter will be value -->

db.collectionName.updateOne()
db.collectionName.updateMany()

<!-- Example -->

db.collectionName.updateOne({\_id: ObjectId("23746238434")}, {$set: { 'price': 45 }})

<!-- Instead of id we can use any field like name, category and any unique identity -->
